<style>
          
    [data-ox-dropdown-button]:focus {
        outline: var(--focus-width) solid var(--focus-color);
        outline-offset: var(--focus-offset);
    }

    
    [data-ox-dropdown-menu] {
        display: none; 
    }

    [data-ox-dropdown-menu] li a:focus {
      outline-offset: calc(-1 * var(--focus-offset));
    }

    [data-ox-dropdown-menu][data-ox-dropdown-show="true"] {
        display: block;
    }

    @media (max-width: 991px) {
      [data-ox-dropdown-container] {
           display: block; 
      }
      
      [data-ox-dropdown-button][aria-expanded="true"] {
           border-bottom-left-radius: 0;
           border-bottom-right-radius: 0;
      }
    }

</style>

props.name: code
props.value:
<script>
    // Initialize all dropdown components on the page.
    document.querySelectorAll('[data-ox-dropdown-container]').forEach(container => {
        const button = container.querySelector('[data-ox-dropdown-button]');
        const menu = container.querySelector('[data-ox-dropdown-menu]');
        const menuItems = menu.querySelectorAll('[role="menuitem"]');
        const configuredTrigger = container.dataset.oxDropdownTrigger || 'click'; // Read configured trigger
        let closeTimeout; // Timeout ID for hover delay

        // Determine if the primary input mechanism supports hover.
        const supportsHover = window.matchMedia('(hover: hover)').matches;

        // Use hover trigger ONLY if configured AND supported, otherwise fallback to click.
        const effectiveTrigger = (configuredTrigger === 'hover' && supportsHover) ? 'hover' : 'click';

        // Toggle the menu's visibility and ARIA state.
        function toggleMenu(show) {
            const isShown = menu.dataset.oxDropdownShow === 'true';
            const targetState = typeof show === 'boolean' ? show : !isShown; 
            
            menu.dataset.oxDropdownShow = targetState ? 'true' : 'false'; 
            button.setAttribute('aria-expanded', targetState);

             if (!targetState) {
                delete menu.dataset.oxDropdownShow;
             }
        }

        // --- Event Listener Setup based on Effective Trigger Type ---

        if (effectiveTrigger === 'hover') {
            // HOVER: Open on entering container, close on leaving (with delay)
            container.addEventListener('mouseenter', () => {
                clearTimeout(closeTimeout); 
                toggleMenu(true); 
            });

            container.addEventListener('mouseleave', () => {
                closeTimeout = setTimeout(() => {
                    toggleMenu(false);
                }, 150); 
            });

            // Keyboard can still open hover menus
            button.addEventListener('keydown', (event) => {
                if ( (event.key === 'Enter' || event.key === ' ') && menu.dataset.oxDropdownShow !== 'true') {
                    event.preventDefault(); 
                    toggleMenu(true);
                    if (menuItems.length > 0) menuItems[0].focus(); 
                }
            });

        } else { 
            // CLICK (default or fallback): Use mousedown for responsiveness
            button.addEventListener('mousedown', (event) => {
                event.stopPropagation(); 
                toggleMenu(); 
                if (menu.dataset.oxDropdownShow === 'true' && menuItems.length > 0) {
                    setTimeout(() => { menuItems[0].focus(); }, 0); 
                }
            });
             // Keyboard support for click mode
            button.addEventListener('keydown', (event) => {
                if ( (event.key === 'Enter' || event.key === ' ') && menu.dataset.oxDropdownShow !== 'true') {
                     event.preventDefault(); 
                     toggleMenu(true);
                     if (menuItems.length > 0) menuItems[0].focus(); 
                 }
            });
        }

        // --- Common Event Listeners (Apply to both modes) ---

        // Handle keyboard navigation within the menu.
        menu.addEventListener('keydown', (event) => {
            if (menuItems.length === 0) return; 

            const currentFocusIndex = Array.from(menuItems).indexOf(document.activeElement);

            switch (event.key) {
                case 'ArrowDown':
                    event.preventDefault(); 
                    menuItems[(currentFocusIndex + 1) % menuItems.length].focus();
                    break;
                case 'ArrowUp':
                    event.preventDefault(); 
                    menuItems[(currentFocusIndex - 1 + menuItems.length) % menuItems.length].focus();
                    break;
                case 'Escape':
                    toggleMenu(false); 
                    button.focus(); 
                    break;
                case 'Home': 
                    event.preventDefault();
                    if (menuItems.length > 0) menuItems[0].focus();
                    break;
                case 'End': 
                    event.preventDefault();
                     if (menuItems.length > 0) menuItems[menuItems.length - 1].focus();
                    break;
                case 'Tab': 
                    toggleMenu(false); // Close on Tab
                    break;
            }
        });

        // Close menu if clicking outside the container.
        document.addEventListener('click', (event) => {
            if (menu.dataset.oxDropdownShow === 'true' && !container.contains(event.target)) {
                 toggleMenu(false); 
            }
        });

        // Handle Escape keydown on the button itself.
        button.addEventListener('keydown', (event) => {
             if (event.key === 'Escape' && menu.dataset.oxDropdownShow === 'true') {
                 toggleMenu(false);
             }
             // Allow ArrowDown to open menu from button.
             if ( event.key === 'ArrowDown' && menu.dataset.oxDropdownShow !== 'true') {
                 event.preventDefault(); 
                 toggleMenu(true);
                 if (menuItems.length > 0) menuItems[0].focus(); 
             }
        });

    }); 

</script>

<style>
  
  [ox-menu-line="top"],
  [ox-menu-line="middle"],
  [ox-menu-line="bottom"] {
    transition: transform 150ms ease;
  }

  [ox-menu-line="middle"] {
    transition: width 150ms ease-in-out;
  }

  [ox-menu-button][data-state="open"] [ox-menu-line="top"] {
    transform: translateY(8px) rotate(45deg);
  }

  [ox-menu-button][data-state="open"] [ox-menu-line="bottom"] {
    transform: translateY(-8px) rotate(-45deg);
  }

  [ox-menu-button][data-state="open"] [ox-menu-line="middle"] {
    width: 0;
  }

</style>

<style>

    [data-ox-dropdown-button]:focus {
        outline: var(--focus-width) solid transparent;
        outline-offset: var(--focus-offset);
    }

    [data-ox-dropdown-menu] {
        display: none;
    }

    [data-ox-dropdown-menu] li a:focus {
      outline-offset: calc(-1 * var(--focus-offset));
    }

    [data-ox-dropdown-menu][data-ox-dropdown-show="true"] {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
    }


    [data-ox-dropdown-icon]  svg {
      transition: transform 300ms cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
    }

    [data-ox-dropdown-button][aria-expanded="true"] > [data-ox-dropdown-icon] svg {
         transform: rotate(180deg);
    }

    @media (max-width: 991px) {
      [data-ox-dropdown-container] {
           display: block;
      }

      [data-ox-dropdown-button][aria-expanded="true"] {
           border-bottom-left-radius: 0;
           border-bottom-right-radius: 0;
      }
    }

</style>

  [ox-menu-button][data-state="open"] [ox-menu-line="bottom"] {
    transform: translateY(-8px) rotate(-45deg);
  }

  [ox-menu-button][data-state="open"] [ox-menu-line="middle"] {
    width: 0;

How is this different from SEO?

On Google, people search with short, generic keywords like “best bank.” In AI tools like ChatGPT or Perplexity, they describe their situation in detail and the LLM tailors the answer based on context it already knows. For example, if someone just got into Y Combinator and asks for the best bank, Google might show Chase. ChatGPT might recommend Rho or other startup-friendly banks. We make sure your brand is the one AI knows and cites in those context-aware answers.
Can GEO work alongside my existing SEO strategy?

Absolutely. Think of SEO as helping you rank in Google when people type keywords, and GEO as helping you show up in AI answers when people describe their problems in detail. They work best together. Your existing SEO content can often be adapted for AI by restructuring it for LLM readability, adding the context AI needs to recommend you, and routing agents to a clean markdown version of the page. We have seen clients keep their SEO strategy running while using GEO to win a completely different discovery channel through AI search in ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Gemini.
Will this work if my brand is completely new?

Yes. Unlike Google, where you must be on the first page to be discovered, AI surfaces the most relevant and authoritative answer regardless of brand age. We identify the high-intent questions your target customers are asking, create AI-optimized content to answer them, and route agents to clean markdown versions of your pages. This helps new brands quickly earn citations in ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Gemini, even against established competitors.
Why is now the right time to invest in GEO?

AI tools like ChatGPT, Perplexity, Claude, and Gemini are rapidly becoming the new starting point for brand discovery, with chatbot traffic more than doubling in the past year. Some sites like Zapier now get nearly half their referrals from AI instead of Google. Investing in GEO today lets you capture this shift before competitors do.
How quickly will I see results?

In many cases, results can appear almost instantly once your optimized pages are live and web search is enabled. While competitive queries may take time to win consistently, brands often see their first new citations within days rather than weeks.
